 trade, religious missions, and imperial interests shaped English encounters with the East. Rivaling the Bible as a widespread, flexible vehicle of Western thought, the Classics provided a ready model for portrayal and understanding of the Oriental Other. Such image-making, Toner argues, persists today in some of the ways the West frames its relationship with the Islamic world and the rising powers of India and China. Discussing examples that range from Jacobean travelogues to Hollywood blockbusters, Homer's Turk proves that there is no permanent version of either the ancient past or the East in English writing-the two have been continually reinvented alongside each other.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aBellettrie. 0aClassical literaturexInfluence. 0aGeschichte Asiens. 0aGeschiedschrijving. 0aHistoriographyzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aHistoriography. 0aOrientalismzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aOrientalism. 0aOriëntalisme. 0aReizen. 0aTravel writingzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aTravel writing. 0aTravel. 4aHISTORY / Asia / General. 4aHISTORY / Middle East / General. 4aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical. 4aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2013z978311031712108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2013z978311037490208iTitle is